{
  "texts": [
    "Each meta-atom offers independent 1-bit control over the two independent field polarizations.",
    "The metasurface design follows that outlined in ref.",
    "58 which is based on the coupling between a fixed resonator and a resonator whose resonance is controlled via the bias voltage of a PIN diode.",
    "Under normal incidence, the two possible configurations of a meta-atom roughly mimic Dirichlet and Neuman boundary conditions in the vicinity of our working frequency of 5.2 GHz, as seen in Fig.",
    "Throughout this work, we only use the metasurface's control over one polarization, and we keep its configuration for the other polarization fixed in its \"0\"-state throughout."
  ]
}